Along the lines of this thread, check out chapter 7 in Bruce's book.
Lots of tables reguarding the time, number of processors, and cost as
functions of how fast and how many bits you want to crack.

128 bits takes ~1e26 processors or dollars or what ever units (approximation
in the exponent!) for DES/IDEA like codes.  The *entire* world GNP is only 1e14
US$.  Be tons cheaper to plant an antenna in the terminal than crack any
128 bit code.

Patience, persistence, truth,
Dr. mike
